SUMMARY:St. Patty's Day Bar Crawl - North Jersey
DESCRIPTION:North Jersey Bowling\, Volleyball\, Tennis And More (BVT)\nCom
 e join the group for a St. Patty's Day Bar Crawl in Hoboken.\n\nWe'll be s
 tarting at The Shepherd & the Knucklehead of Hoboken\, 1313 Willow Ave.\, 
 at 6:30 p.m. and then walking around from there.\n\n(tentative schedule be
 low)\n\nOf course\, join us at any time. We'll try to post updates in the 
 comments as the night unfolds. Feel free to call or text Andy Milone at 20
 1-234-9609\, or direct message him on Meetup or on Whatsapp\, if you can't
  find us or have questions.\n\nIt's totally optional to wear your favorite
  St. Patrick's Day attire and/or consume a few adult beverages. Feel free 
 to just come and have a good time hanging with familiar faces and meeting 
 new ones.\n\n**6:30 p.m.**\n\n* The Shepherd & the Knucklehead of Hoboken 
 - 1313 Willow Ave.\n\n**8:30 p.m.**\n\n* The Ale House - 1034 Willow Ave.\
 n\n**9:30 p.m.**\n\n* 10th & Willow Bar & Grill - 935 Willow Ave.\n\n**11:
 30 p.m.**\n\n* Finnegan's Pub - 734 Willow Ave.\n\n**12 a.m.**\n\n* Farsid
 e Tavern - 531 Washington St.\n* Louise & Jerry's - 329 Washington St. (Op
 tional)\n* Black Bear Hoboken Bar & Grill - 205 Washington St. (Optional)\
 n* Mike's Wild Moose Saloon – 92 River St. (Optional)\n\nPlease be smart
  about travel. The train station is not far away and runs late. Parking ca
 n be a challenge\, but there is street parking (where residential permit i
 s not required\, and several paid public parking garages\, including at 11
 2 River St. and 1330 Willow Ave. Feel free to comment below if interested 
 in carpooling.\n\nThis event follows our Halloween and Holiday bar crawls\
 , a trend spurred by Ray and Raymond\, two regular attendees of our events
 .\n\nQuestions? Suggestions? Concerns? You can reach out to Andy Milone at
  201-234-9609 (call/text)\, or by message over Meetup or Whatsapp.
